What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

template <typename T>
T triple(T x)
{
    return x * 3;
}

int main()
{
    std::cout << triple(4) << '\n';
    std::cout << triple(2.5) << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

This template is supposed to return the smaller of two values, but it has a bug. What is it?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

template <typename T>
T minimum(T a, T b)
{
    return (a > b) ? a : b;
}

int main()
{
    std::cout << minimum(3, 7) << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```
